------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party components and their separate licenses
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Runtime dependencies (see package.json / package-lock.json for exact versions),
each under its own license — typically MIT / Apache-2.0 / ISC:

  @larksuiteoapi/node-sdk   Feishu / Lark open-platform SDK
  grammy                    Telegram bot framework
  ollama                    Local Ollama client
  undici                    HTTP client (OpenAI- and Anthropic-compatible API calls)
  node-fetch                HTTP client (media download / URL enrichment)
  https-proxy-agent         Proxy support (Telegram channel)
  dayjs                     Date / timezone handling
  dotenv                    .env loading

Desktop GUI (desktop/) additionally bundles, among others:
  Electron, React, Vite, Monaco Editor, Tailwind CSS, electron-builder,
  electron-updater, react-markdown, highlight.js, lucide-react — each under
  its own license (MIT / Apache-2.0 / BSD).

External tools invoked but NOT bundled (install separately):
  Ollama          local LLM runtime — https://ollama.com
  whisper.cpp     speech-to-text (ASR) — Apache/MIT, https://github.com/ggml-org/whisper.cpp
  ffmpeg          audio/video transcoding — LGPL/GPL, https://ffmpeg.org

LLM providers:
  echolog can run fully local via Ollama, or call a cloud LLM you configure
  (OpenAI-compatible endpoints, or Anthropic's Messages API). When you configure
  a cloud provider, the content you send for diary/weekly generation is
  transmitted to that provider under their terms. Local (Ollama) keeps everything
  on your machine.
